com.tsgrp.migration.queuepop

Class QueuePopulatorXmlWithAssociations

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.event.AbstractListener
      • com.tsgrp.migration.queuepop.QueuePopulatorXml
        • com.tsgrp.migration.queuepop.QueuePopulatorXmlWithAssociations
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PipelinePopulateQueueEventListener

    public class QueuePopulatorXmlWithAssociations
extends QueuePopulatorXml
    QueuePopulator class which loads migration source data from an XML file. This class allows for a document and its associations to be separate nodes in the XML. This class is an extension of QueuePopulatorXml specifically designed to add processing children association Attribute mapping is not specific to the parent nodes or the children nodes, so the schema must be the same otherwise the nodes will not get properly updated with their attributes.

      • setParentNodeXPath

        public void setParentNodeXPath(java.lang.String parentNodeXPath)
        Injected, OPTIONAL. String of the XPath query that will be used to select parent nodes in the XML file to be added as main migration nodes. If left blank it will be assumed that the parent nodes will be populated by the nodeXPathList
        Parameters:
        parentNodeXPath - - XPath query that will be used to find parent nodes in the XML file. Note that the XPath query is relative to the current node (which is the nodeXPath) being parsed in the XML.

      • setChildNodeXPaths

        public void setChildNodeXPaths(java.util.List<java.lang.String> childNodeXPaths)
        Injected, REQUIRED. List of all XPath queries that will be used to select nodes in the XML file to be added as children nodes of the main migration nodes.
        Parameters:
        childNodeXPaths - - XPath queries that will be used to find child nodes in the XML file. Note that the XPath query is relative to the current (parent) node being parsed in the XML.
